132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1293
S.P. 523 In Senate, March 25, 2025
An Act to Prohibit Coyote-killing Contests in Maine
Reference to the Committee on Inland Fisheries and Wildlife suggested and ordered
printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator BEEBE-CENTER of Knox.
Cosponsored by Representative DODGE of Belfast and
Senators: BRENNER of Cumberland, LAWRENCE of York, RAFFERTY of York,
Representatives: BOYER of Cape Elizabeth, FRIEDMANN of Bar Harbor, KUHN of
Falmouth, PUGH of Portland.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 12 MRSA ยง12002 is enacted to read:
3 ยง12002. Coyote-killing contests prohibited
4 1. "Coyote-killing contest" defined. As used in this section, unless the context
5 otherwise indicates, "coyote-killing contest" means an organized or sponsored competition
6 with the objective of killing coyotes for prizes or entertainment.
7 2. Coyote-killing contests prohibited. A person may not:
8 A. Arrange, cause, hold, organize, plan or sponsor a coyote-killing contest;
9 B. Provide the venue for a coyote-killing contest;
10 C. Entice a person to knowingly take part in a coyote-killing contest; or
11 D. Knowingly take part in a coyote-killing contest.
12 A person who violates this subsection commits a Class E crime.
13 3. Defense of person or property and sanctioned culling. This section may not be
14 construed to prohibit a person from protecting a person or property or a municipal, county
15 or state employee's sanctioned culling of coyotes.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This bill prohibits coyote-killing contests. It provides that a person who arranges,
1188 provides a venue for, entices a person to knowingly take part in or knowingly takes part in
1199 a coyote-killing contest commits a Class E crime. It specifies that the law prohibiting
2200 coyote-killing contests may not be construed to prohibit the defense of a person or property
2211 or a government employee's sanctioned culling of coyotes.
